text: i made it with a twist(read it till the end for the twist). only had tej patta, Kali mirch, dalchini and laung in khade masale. i added 6 grated garlic cloves and an inch of ginger afterwards. then one finely chopped onion, fried it till golden. then added powdered masale as you said. afterwards added tomato and green chilli paste, added salt(yes  I added it here so that tomato gets cooked), fried it .added coriander powder and one more as you said..now the gravy got thick so i added chai Patti Pani and covered it for 5 mins, added chhole, then more water, I didn't use baking soda... whistled it as you said.. now the twist! i added two teaspoons of imli chutney which I got with kachori and mirchbada from a shop as my breakfast. i whistled it twice on high flame. mashed some of the chholes. served it with rice, chapati and salad. tasted delicious.
